Name: Nutrient Bar
Description: A nourishing nutrient paste, sandwiched between thin wafer layers.

Name: Mush Bar
Description:
An edible, putrefied mudslop.

Mush Bars are preferable to starvation, but only just barely.

Name: Meal Lice
Description: A flavorless grain that almost never wiggles on its own.

Name: Muckroot
Description:
A seedless fruit with an upsettingly bland aftertaste.

It cannot be replanted.

Digging up Buried Objects may uncover a Muckroot.

Name: Hexalent Fruit
Description:
A seedless fruit with an unusual rubbery texture.

It cannot be replanted.

Hexalent fruit is much more calorie dense than Muckroot fruit.

Name: Mushroom
Description: An edible, flavorless fungus that grew in the dark.

Name: Lettuce
Description: Crunchy, slightly salty leaves from a Waterweed plant.

Name: Meat
Description: Uncooked meat from a very dead critter. Yum!

Name: Bristle Berry
Description: A sweet, mostly pleasant-tasting fruit covered in prickly barbs.

Name: Pacu Fillet
Description: An uncooked fillet from a very dead Pacu. Yum!

Name: Pickled Meal
Description:
Meal Lice preserved in vinegar.

It's a rarely acquired taste.

Name: Liceloaf
Description: Meal Lice compacted into a dense, immobile loaf.

Name: Mush Fry
Description:
Deep fried, solidified mudslop.

The inside is almost completely uncooked, despite the crunch on the outside.

Name: Gristle Berry
Description:
The grilled bud of a Bristle Berry.

Heat unlocked an exquisite taste in the fruit, though the burnt spines leave something to be desired.

Name: Fried Mushroom
Description:
A fried dish made with a fruiting Dusk Cap.

It has a thick, savory flavor with subtle earthy undertones.

Name: Frost Bun
Description:
A simple bun baked from Sleet Wheat Grain grain.

Each bite leaves a mild cooling sensation in one's mouth, even when the bun itself is warm.

Name: Omelette
Description:
Fluffed and folded Egg innards.

It turns out you do, in fact, have to break a few eggs to make it.

Name: Cooked Fish
Description:
The cooked Fillet of a freshly caught Pacu.

Unsurprisingly, it tastes a bit fishy.

Name: Barbeque
Description:
The cooked meat of a defeated critter.

It has a delightful smoky aftertaste.

Name: Berry Sludge
Description:
A mashed up Bristle Berry sludge with an exceptionally long shelf life.

Its aggressive, overbearing sweetness can leave the tongue feeling temporarily numb.

Name: Stuffed Berry
Description: A baked Bristle Berry stuffed with delectable spices and vibrantly flavored.

Name: Surf'n'Turf
Description:
A bit of Meat from the land and Fish from the sea.

It hearty and satisfying.

Name: Mushroom Wrap
Description:
Flavorful Mushrooms wrapped in Lettuce.

It has an earthy flavor punctuated by a refreshing crunch.

Name: Tofu
Description:
A bland curd made from Nosh Beans.

It has an unusual but pleasant consistency.

Name: Pepper Bread
Description:
A loaf of bread, lightly spiced with Pincha Peppernut for a mild bite.

There's a simple joy to be had in pulling it apart in one's fingers.

Name: Spicy Tofu
Description:
Tofu marinated in a flavorful Pincha Pepperplant sauce.

It packs a delightful punch.

Name: Frost Burger
Description:
Meat and Lettuce on a chilled Frost Bun.

It's the only burger ever to be served cold.

Name: Nosh Bean
Description: An inedible bean that can be processed into delicious foods.

Name: Pincha Peppernut
Description:
The flavorful nut of a Pincha Pepperplant.

The bitter outer rind hides a rich, peppery core that is useful in cooking.

Name: Sleet Wheat Grain
Description: An edible grain that leaves a cool taste on the tongue.

Name: Raw Egg
Description:
A raw Egg that has been cracked open for use in Food preparation.

It will never hatch.
